## E2E default-to-int workspace (round 10 follow-up)

**Context:** The round-10 round showed that the e2e suite's default fake creds caused 6 of 80 tests to time out on Databricks-dependent routes. Manual real-creds invocation made them pass. The right answer is to make int the **default** so a plain `pytest tests/e2e/` is a real signal, not a half-broken run.

**Change:**

`tests/e2e/conftest.py` — the `_set_env` fixture now mints a workspace OAuth token from the Databricks CLI profile named by `ONTOBRICKS_E2E_PROFILE` (default `fevm-ontobricks-int`) and exports it as `DATABRICKS_HOST`/`DATABRICKS_TOKEN` into the subprocess. Three operating modes:

| Mode | Trigger | Behaviour |
|---|---|---|
| Auto-int (default) | nothing | mint OAuth from the configured profile; uses warehouse `fcdf5a06992ad225` |
| Caller creds | `DATABRICKS_HOST` + `DATABRICKS_TOKEN` already set | respect them, set warehouse override if `ONTOBRICKS_E2E_WAREHOUSE_ID` is supplied |
| Fake | `ONTOBRICKS_E2E_FAKE_CREDS=1` | use the original `test.databricks.com` fake values (6 DB tests will time out — intentional for non-int CI) |
| Skip | no working profile + no `_FAKE_CREDS` opt-in | skip the suite with an actionable error message |

**Verification:**

```
# Default — int workspace, no env-var ritual required.
uv run pytest tests/e2e/ --no-cov -q
# 80 passed in 59.86s

# Fake-creds opt-out still works.
ONTOBRICKS_E2E_FAKE_CREDS=1 uv run pytest tests/e2e/test_e2e_flows.py::TestNavigation -q
# 1 failed, 8 passed (the /dtwin/ test times out as expected)

# Bad profile -> graceful skip with actionable error.
ONTOBRICKS_E2E_PROFILE=does-not-exist uv run pytest tests/e2e/test_e2e_flows.py::TestNavigation -q
# 6 skipped
```

**Files modified:**

- `tests/e2e/conftest.py` — `_mint_workspace_token` helper + 3-mode `_set_env` fixture.
- `changelogs/2026-05-14.log` — this entry.
